Development of epidemic situation

1. Hubei Health Commission: Not Allowed to reduce the number of confirmed cases. Tu Yuanchao, deputy director of the Hubei Health Commission, said at a press conference on February 21 that reductions in confirmed cases would not be allowed and that all reductions must be added back. Previously, the number of newly confirmed cases in Hubei Province and Wuhan had fluctuated greatly due to the negative increase in the number of new cases due to the repeated changes in the statistical standards and the reduction of confirmed cases in Huangshi, Tianmen and other places.

2. There were 514 cases reported by prisons in three provinces of Hubei, Shandong and Zhejiang in one day. Five prisons in Hubei, Shandong and Zhejiang were found to have clusters of new coronary pneumonia, all of which were imported cases. As of the 21st, 230 cases had been confirmed in Wuhan Women's prison, 41 in Hanjin prison, 207 in Rencheng District prison and 34 in Shilifeng prison, which were imported by a police officer who concealed his travel history. Eleven officials, including the Shandong Justice Minister, were removed from their posts.

3. A total of 346 cases of new coronary pneumonia were confirmed in Korea. As of 9 a.m. on February 22, a total of 346 cases of COVID-19 infection (COVID-19) had been reported in South Korea, including two deaths. The south-east Taegu was hit hardest by the COVID-19 outbreak, with a massive outbreak. One of the patients, a 61-year-old man, recently attended the new World Taegu Church, where 43 people have been diagnosed and about 400 have developed symptoms, 9,000 members were told to segregate themselves.

The Seoul Metropolitan Government announced that it would ban rallies in the city's three main squares and close religious facilities; three soldiers in the South Korean military have been diagnosed with the disease, and all military bases are under emergency lockdown and have been upgraded to dangerous. At a press conference on the morning of February 22, Deputy Minister of the Central Emergency Management Department, Jin Gangli, said that the epidemic has not yet entered the stage of spreading throughout the country, the government decided to maintain the second-highest alert level for COVID-19(COVID-19) .

4. As new coronaviruses spread across the Middle East, World Health Organization warns, "window of opportunity is narrowing. ". On February 21, new cases were reported in the United Arab Emirates, Iran, Israel and Lebanon. Of these, 13 new Iranian cases were found in Qom (7) , Tehran (4) and Jiran (2) . Minou Mohrez, an Iranian health ministry official, said on Feb. 21 that the outbreak had now spread to several Iranian cities, including the capital, Tehran, "probably from Chinese workers who work in Qom and have traveled to China, " according to Caixin. A Chinese company is said to be building a solar power plant in Qom.

As of February 21,32 cases had been reported from five countries in the Middle East: the United Arab Emirates (11 cases) , Egypt (1 case) , Iran (18 cases, 4 deaths) , Israel (1 case) and Lebanon (1 case) . "The window of opportunity is narrowing, so we need to act quickly before it closes completely... " the World Health Organization Organization warns

5. World Health Organization organized a team of experts to go to Wuhan on February 22. On the afternoon of February 21, Central European time, the director-general of the World Health Organization, Tan Desai, announced at a regular press conference on the epidemic situation of Xinguan, that after the study tour in Beijing, Guangdong and Sichuan, a team of about 20 experts from World Health Organization and the Chinese will enter Wuhan, Hubei Province, on February 22 to continue its work. Until now, China and World Health Organization had only announced that the team would be visiting Beijing, Sichuan and Guangdong. They arrived in China over the weekend and have been working since February 17. Their academic fields include epidemiology, virology, clinical management, outbreak control and public health. Their main work is to study the spread of the virus dynamics, the severity of the epidemic, China's response strategies, and the effectiveness of measures implemented. The objective of the expert group is to rapidly develop follow-up steps to respond to the new outbreak in China and around the world.

6. A doctor of Wuhan Red Cross Hospital died of new pneumonia. On Feb. 21, the Wuhan Red Cross Hospital issued a public notice confirming that its general surgeon, Xiao Jun, was fighting the epidemic with a first line infection of new crown pneumonia, according to the public account on Wechat of the hospital, died at Kam Yin Tam Hospital, Wuhan at 18:13 on 8 February 2020.

Kill. 66 people in Beijing close contact after home quarantine. Pang Xinghuo, deputy director of the Beijing Center for Disease Control and Prevention, introduced a case. On February 13, the center received a diagnosis of new coronary pneumonia and confirmed that his daughter B was a close contact, but because B was breastfeeding, she was isolated at home. But B later hid the sore throat until Feb. 19, when he was diagnosed with a new case of pneumonia, when the CDC began screening close contacts. The investigation found that B has resumed work, and finally designated 66 people as close contacts, in addition to more than 200 general contacts, isolated at home.

8. Heilongjiang is also the worst affected region. Heilongjiang, far from Wuhan, has become one of the hardest hit areas by accident, with the number of confirmed cases approaching 500. The number of severe cases is now second only to Hubei, with the third highest death toll in the country. The mortality rate is comparable to that of Hubei (except Wuhan)  Local epidemic control measures lag, medical treatment resources are tight and unbalanced.

9.33 community workers killed. On February 21, Chen Yueliang, director of the Department of grass-roots political power construction and community governance of the Ministry of Civil Affairs, gave a press conference on the joint prevention and control mechanism of the State Council, "As of February 20,33 community workers in urban and rural areas have died in the line of duty during the epidemic prevention and control period. "

10. One new case of Shennongjia was diagnosed, with an incubation period of up to 27 days. According to Hubei Daily, the patient returned to Songbai town in Shennongjia from Huarong District in a private car on January 24. He developed fever, body temperature 37.5 °C and fatigue on the night of February 19 and went to the People's Hospital in the forest region on February 20. The patient's family stayed with her sister while she was in Ezhou. Her sister became ill on January 25 and was confirmed as a new case of pneumonia in Ezhou on February 2. No new cases have been confirmed in the Shennongjia for 16 days since February 3. If the patient returns from Ezhou to February 19, the incubation period is up to 27 days.

Future Studies

CDC: COVID-19. The U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) warned Feb. 21 that COVID-19 could spread in the United States, and U.S. health officials are preparing for a possible new pandemic. As of the 21st, a total of 34 confirmed cases of new pneumonia were found in the United States, including 18 cases from the "Diamond Princess" cruise ship. "No new coronavirus has been detected in the U.S. community, but it could eventually happen, " said Nancy Messonnier, director of the CDC's respiratory disease. "Our goal is to continue to slow the spread of the new coronavirus in the United States to buy more time to prepare for a possible sustained spread. "

Hu Yabo, a member of the Standing Committee of the Wuhan Municipal Party Committee and Executive Vice Mayor of the Wuhan Municipal Government, said on February 21 that the city planned to build 19 more shelter hospitals, with 30,000 shelter hospital beds to be stored in Wuhan by February 25. According to its introduction, at present Wuhan already had 13 shelter hospitals to open the cabin, may provide the rescue bed to reach 13,348, already used 9,313. 72 Support Wuhan Medical Team to enter the shelter hospital.

2. Patients discharged from hospital with new pneumonia were put under isolation for 14 days. On February 22, Wuhan issued a notice on the isolation of discharged patients with newly cured pneumonia, new champion pneumonia discharged patients "should be designated places for 14 days of unified implementation of free rehabilitation isolation and medical observation. Observation period, physical conditions meet the conditions of release of isolation. ". Earlier, a case in Chengdu showed that nucleic acid testing was still positive 10 days after discharge.

3. The contradiction between supply and demand of medical materials is prominent in Hubei Province. Hubei Province held a press conference on the prevention and control of the new crown pneumonia epidemic. Cao Guangjing, vice governor of Hubei Province, said that at present, the supply and demand of medical materials in Hubei Province are still relatively tight. In order to deal with this situation, Hubei Province issued a document, expanding the supply of medical supplies through the "three-in-one" initiative. Cao Guangjing introduced that specifically, it includes "promoting a group" , that is, promoting capable enterprises to expand production and increase production capacity; "transferring production to a group" , that is, relevant enterprises can transfer production when they meet product quality requirements, for example, the original production of civilian mask enterprises to produce medical masks, the former production of clothing enterprises to produce medical protective clothing. In addition, Hubei Province still wants"new build a batch", namely the enterprise is willing to invest capital to build new medical material factory.

On the other hand, in order to cope with the tight hotel accommodation in Wuhan, seven "Three Gorges cruises" operated by Ministry of Transport of the People's Republic of China provide accommodation for medical staff, with a total capacity of 1,469 beds. Among them, the Blue Whale has docked at the Wangs Lane Pier in Kong Hon.

5. Restaurants in Guangzhou resume dining hall, part of the county and urban areas may not be table. On February 21, following the publication of the relevant guidelines for the resumption of work in the catering industry in Guangdong Province, the office of the COVID-19 recently issued the guidelines for the orderly resumption of work in the catering industry in Guangzhou (for trial implementation) , nansha, Conghua and Zengcheng are designated as grade IV zones, while the remaining eight zones are all grade III zones. For counties (cities and districts) classified as Level III prevention and control areas, catering business units restrict dining services, including the prohibition of table-sharing; the actual number of dining tables in the lobby shall not exceed 50% of normal use, and the distance between different dining tables shall not be less than 1 meter; Long table with rows of customers sitting next to each other, opposite the staggered sitting; round table customers sitting next to each other, face-to-face distance of not less than 1 meters.

Kill. Hong Kong to launch 'super computer' to track outbreak. On February 21, Hong Kong's Centre for Health Protection said it had asked the police to activate the critical incident investigation and disaster support system, commonly known as the "supercomputer" system, because of the increased number and complexity of new cases, assist in tracking patients'movements and close contacts. The "Super Computer" system is mainly used for data management and analysis to support the investigation of criminal cases. In the third-generation major incident investigation and disaster support system launched in 2016, the "infectious disease infection tracking" function has been introduced, to assist the Centre for Health Protection in tracking and analysis of infectious diseases. The supercomputer system can also analyze whether there is an association between different confirmed cases.

To cancel the requirement for every household to go out every two days to purchase goods and materials in small areas where no epidemic has occurred and where there are no close contacts, and to resume normal production and living order in an orderly manner.

Medical Solution

1. The latest study found no direct relationship between the new coronavirus and the Pangolin. On February 20, a paper on Pangolin coronavirus was published on Biorxiv, a preprint website, by a team led by Shen Yongyi and Xiao Lihua of the South China Agricultural University, as well as Chen Jinping, deputy director of the Guangdong Institute of Biological Resources Application. Both teams found that the Pangolin virus was unlikely to be directly related to the new coronavirus, but that another intermediate host between the two viruses may have been involved in reprogramming the virus. The researchers suggest that some pangolin coronavirus s proteins have receptor binding domains that are almost identical to those of the new coronavirus, so the new coronavirus may have originated from a recombination of the Pangolin coronavirus with the bat-derived rsg13 virus. A study by Guan's team on February 19 found that the coronavirus in the pangolin sample was 97 percent similar to the new coronavirus. But they could not rule out the possibility that the Pangolin was infected with a virus similar to the new coronavirus, independent of its bat or other animal host.

2. New Research suggests that npv from a non-primary source in the south China Seafood Market had human-to-human transmission in early December. On February 21st researchers at the Chinese Academy of Sciences, South China Agricultural University and the Chinese Brain Science Institute, among others, published a preprint suggesting that the new coronavirus from the south China Seafood Market in Wuhan had been introduced from elsewhere, crowded markets facilitated the spread of the virus throughout the city in early December 2019. The paper also showed that the new coronavirus had two significant population expansions before February 12, with the early expansion occurring on December 8 and the recent expansion on January 6. The paper collected virus data that had been shared worldwide with the ISAID EpiFluTM database as of February 12, including 93 new coronavirus samples from 12 countries on four continents. Published on Chinese Academy of Sciences, Without Peer Review.

3. Zhong Nanshan's team isolated the virus from urine. According to Guangzhou Daily News, at 10:00 am on February 22, Guangzhou City held Guangzhou City Science and technology battle "epidemic" News, briefing Guangzhou City Prevention and control of new pneumonia research work measures, achievements and so on. In carrying out research on the origin of the virus, academician Zhong Nanshan's team expert, Professor Zhao Jincun, deputy director of the state key laboratory of respiratory disease, successfully isolated the COVID-19 strain (COVID-19) for the first time in conjunction with the Guangzhou Customs, it will lay a foundation for further research on vaccines and drugs. The team then isolated COVID-19(COVID-19) from stool samples from patients with NCP. Recently, they once again isolated the new coronavirus from the urine of patients with NCP, which has important warning and guiding significance for Public Health Safety Prevention and control. At present, the related research group is focusing on the pathogenesis of the virus and drug treatment targets.

Peripheral influence

1. Human Social Department: The Enterprise employee infects the new crown pneumonia not to be able to determine the work injury. The Ministry of Human and Social Affairs said on February 21 that in the prevention and treatment of new-crown pneumonia, medical care and related staff due to the performance of their duties, infection of new-crown pneumonia or death due to new-crown pneumonia, should be considered as work-related injuries. Infection with NCP can not be considered an injury at work if it is not performed by staff involved in NCP prevention and related work.

2. Morgan Stanley estimates China's first quarter GDP may be as low as 3.5% . China's economic growth could slow to 3.5 percent in the first quarter if the outbreak is not brought under control fast enough to return manufacturing to normal levels, according to a Morgan Stanley study released Feb. 19. While local governments are easing restrictions on production halts, available macrocosm and microcosm data show a slow recovery in production activity in China, the report said. Output levels last week were just 30-50 per cent of normal levels and were expected to reach 60-80 per cent of normal levels by the end of February before returning to normal in mid-to-late March, according to Morgan Stanley China industry analysts. If the spread of the disease is not controlled over the next two weeks, disruption to production could continue into the second quarter of this year.

3. Haidilao has received 2.1 billion yuan in credit. On February 21, caixin reporter learned from Haidilao that Haidilao has received 2.1 billion yuan in credit support from the Beijing branch of Citic Bank and Baixin Bank, the first loan of $810 million was transferred to the Haidilao account on February 19. Haidilao has been closed for nearly a month, citic construction investment research reported that its annual revenue will lose 6.1 billion yuan, recently part of the delivery business recovery.

4. The overall resumption rate of major express delivery enterprises is nearly 70% . According to Wu Chungeng, director of the Ministry of Transport of the People's Republic of China, the express delivery industry has recovered steadily, with China Post, SF express and Jd.com all returning to work, and other major express delivery companies returning to work with an overall rate of 66.7 percent.

5. Shanghai suspends on-the-spot Recruitment of university graduates. Shanghai Municipal Education Commission issued a notice on the 2020 Shanghai City College graduates to make arrangements for employment. According to the notice, all universities, postgraduate training units and employment service departments in all districts shall suspend all on-the-spot recruitment activities for graduates and shall not receive any lectures from employing units To suspend the organization and implementation of Shanghai 2020 public institutions concentrated open recruitment examination and "three support one support" personnel recruitment.

After investigation, the two have three organizations, vehicles to Huanggang City in Hubei Province, and other epidemic areas of flour, vegetables and other supplies. 2. The civil servant who reprimanded the nurse was suspended for examination. On Feb. 20, a video of a patient needlessly reprimanding a nurse for cleaning a toilet went viral on social media. After the nurse told her that she had helped contact the patient, the patient remained surly. On February 21, the Hubei Provincial Bureau of Market Supervision announced that the patient was Zhu Baohua, deputy director of the Preparatory Group of the Bureau's Logistics Service Center. After the incident, Zhu Baohua posted an apology on Wechat, a social media platform, to the medical staff who were reprimanded, saying that "after recovery, he will respond to the call to donate blood to fight the epidemic.
